Galkovsky has an article about HG Wells and how he described 19th century England as basically a caste society: e.g. Wells talks about how he was not allowed to play with the "simple" children below his social status and how those "above" him acted arrogant to him in their turn.

Meanwhile it turns out he was talking about neighbors on a single street with everyone being basically equal. His mother forced him to wear a coat at all times outside so no one could see his cheap shirt below, they pretended to have servants in front of others. Insane existence.
